QUESTION ==>>

-------------Path to follow maximum fruit in a matrix-------------
PROBLEM STATEMENT
A man wants to collect the maximum amount of fruit, tell them which path to followGiven a matrix representing a fruit tree
with walls and paths, the task is to find the path that collects the maximum number of fruits. The fruits are represented
by their names in the matrix, walls are represented by the string "wall", and empty paths are represented by the string 
"path". If there is no fruit in the matrix, return null.


INPUT FORMAT
The first line of input contains an integer N, representing the number of rows in the matrix.The second line of input
contains an integer M, representing the number of columns in the matrix.The third line of input contains space-seperated a
list of strings representing the matrix.Note: The matrix is of size N x M.


OUTPUT FORMAT
Display a List of strings, where each fruit in the path is separated by '-->'. If no fruit is present in the matrix, return
null.


CONSTRAINTS
1 < N <= 10^2
1 < M <= 10^2


SAMPLE TESTCASE 0
Testcase Input
6
6
wall wall wall wall wall wall
wall wall wall wall wall wall
wall wall wall wall wall wall
wall wall wall wall path wall
wall wall wall wall wall wall
wall wall wall wall wall wall
Testcase Output
null
Explanation
No fruitâ€™s are present in matrix


SAMPLE TESTCASE 1
Testcase Input
6
6
apple banana lemon wall wall apple
wall wall banana wall wall banana
wall wall apple apple apple apple
wall wall wall wall path wall
mango lemon wall wall wall apple
wall wall wall wall wall wall
Testcase Output
apple --> banana --> lemon --> banana --> apple --> apple --> apple --> apple --> banana --> apple
Explanation
Starting at apple at position (0, 0).
Move right to banana at position (0, 1).
Continue to lemon at position (0, 2).
Move down to banana at position (1, 2).
Continue down to apple at position (2, 2).
Move right, collecting four apples consecutively from (2, 3) to (2, 5).
Then move up to banana at position (1, 5), and finish at apple at position (0, 5).
